    "snippet": "Clean Access Desert Initiative (CADI) baseline map for Wake and Durham Counties, North Carolina. \n\nThis web map identifies spatial disparities in access to public restrooms by integrating restroom availability (density and count) with community vulnerability indicators, including poverty levels, vehicle access, and age-related vulnerability. \n\nEach census tract is classified into Low, Moderate, or High priority zones based on a composite CADI score (0–1), where higher values indicate greater need for improved restroom access. \n\nThis map supports planning, equity analysis, and decision-making by highlighting areas with critical infrastructure gaps and enabling further scenario-based analysis through associated geoprocessing tools.",
